===Adjective===
'''either''' (''not [[comparable]]'')

# one or the other (of two)
#:''I don't mind whether your mother or father attends - you can bring '''either''' parent.''
# each of two
#:''The room has a door at '''either''' end.''

====Synonyms====
* (''one or the other''): 
* (''each of two''): [[both]], [[each]]

