===Pronoun===
'''either'''

# one or the other (of two)
#:''I don't mind whether your mother or father attends - you can bring '''either'''.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
*French: [[l'un ou l'autre]] ''m'', l'une ou l'autre ''f'' (''for two feminine nouns'')
{{mid}}
